text: Grahamville is an unincorporated community in McCracken County, in the U.S. state of Kentucky. ==History== Grahamville was platted in 1877 by Zelotes Cllinton Graham, who gave the community his last name. A post office called Grahamville was established in 1888, and remained in operation until 1909. A variant name was "Grahamsville". ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in McCracken County, Kentucky Category:Unincorporated communities in Kentucky
title: Grahamville, Kentucky
